articles.author: WAFAA SHURAFA
articles.description: WADI GAZA, Gaza Strip (AP) — A ship carrying 200 tons of aid approached the coast of Gaza on Friday in a mission to inaugurate a sea route from Cyprus that was intended to bring more assistance to alleviate the humanitarian crisis in the enclave five months into the war between Israel and Hamas.
articles.title: The first ship to use a new sea route approaches Gaza with 200 tons of aid

articles.author: ERIC TUCKER, ALANNA DURKIN RICHER and TERRY SPENCER
articles.description: FORT PIERCE, Fla. (AP) — A federal judge on Thursday rejected one bid by Donald Trump to throw out out his classified documents criminal case, and appeared skeptical during hours of arguments of a separate effort to scuttle the prosecution ahead of trial.
articles.title: Judge rejects bid by Donald Trump to throw out classified documents case on constitutional grounds

articles.author: DASHA LITVINOVA
articles.description: Russia began three days of voting Friday in a presidential election that is all but certain to extend President Vladimir Putin’s rule by six more years after he stifled dissent.
articles.title: Russians are voting in an election that holds little suspense after Putin crushed dissent

articles.author: LORI HINNANT, VASILISA STEPANENKO, SAMYA KULLAB and HANNA ARHIROVA
articles.description: KYIV, Ukraine (AP) — He and his parents were among the last in their village to take a Russian passport, but the pressure was becoming unbearable.By his third beating at the hands of the Russian soldiers occupying Ukraine’s Kherson region, Vyacheslav Ryabkov caved.
articles.title: Using coercion, Russia has successfully imposed its citizenship in Ukraine’s occupied territories

articles.description: WINCHESTER, Ind. (AP) — Police in Ohio confirmed two deaths resulting from a fierce storm system that unleashed suspected twisters and damaged homes and businesses in parts of Ohio, Kentucky and Indiana on Thursday.
articles.title: Ohio police confirm 2 dead in fierce storm that damaged homes and businesses in 3 states

articles.author: HYUNG-JIN KIM
articles.description: SEOUL, South Korea (AP) — Shohei Ohtani and his wife arrived in South Korea with his Los Angeles Dodgers teammates on Friday ahead of their season-opening games with the San Diego Padres next week.
articles.title: Baseball superstar Ohtani and his wife arrive in South Korea for Dodgers-Padres MLB opener

articles.description: LONDON (AP) — System outages at McDonald's have been reported worldwide Friday, shuttering some restaurants and leading to social media complaints, while other locations were back up and running after the failures.
articles.title: McDonald's system outages are reported worldwide. Some restaurants are back

articles.author: JON GAMBRELL
articles.description: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates (AP) — A suspected attack by Yemen's Houthi rebels struck a tanker in the Red Sea early Friday, causing damage to the vessel while the crew was reported unharmed, authorities said.
articles.title: Suspected attack by Yemen's Houthi rebels strikes a ship in the Red Sea, though crew reportedly safe

articles.author: JOSH BOAK
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Lori Shelton can't fathom ever having the money to buy a home — and that's a major reason why so many voters feel down on the economy ahead of this year's presidential election.Shelton, 67, drives an Uber to help pay rent in Aurora, Colorado.
articles.title: Why are so many voters frustrated by the US economy? It's home prices
